title: Ohio State trying to improve production in red zone
text:
Posted: 1:16 p.m. Friday, Oct. 9, 2015 Ohio State trying to improve production in red zone Staff Writer COLUMBUS â€” 
Ohio State has stood atop the college football world for nine months. It took the throne on Jan. 12 in Texas. It polished the crown throughout the offseason and has protected it now for five weeks in the regular season. 
The No. 1 Buckeyes were a unanimous No. 1 team in August. They are no more. Five teams received No. 1 votes in the Associated Press poll this week.
